===Noun===
'''{{PAGENAME}}'''
# 1.) A sloppily cut groove, furrow, or trench, characterised by the presence of refuse material from which it was cut.  Same root as scoria, which dictionary.com defines as "the refuse of a smelted metal or ore; slag."  

"The tracks of his father's foot were gone.  Where they had been were now long, watercloudy '''scoriations''' resembling the sporadic course of a Lilliputian mowing machine." ~William Faulkner

2.)  An anthropological term used to describe grooves or other similiar markings in exclusively bullets.  Scoriation is a joining of "scoring" and "striation." (Arp, Don Jr., "BATTLEFIELD ODDITIES:
EXPLAINING TWO MINIÉ BALLS FROM PEA RIDGE NATIONAL MILITARY PARK."  [[The Nebraska Anthropologist]].  Vol. 17, Number 1.  URL: http://www.unl.edu/anthro/anthrogroup/nebraska_anthropologist/issue_archive/01_02.pdf